notes.text:
This update for GraphicsMagick fixes the following issues:
  - Memory allocation failure in AcquireMagickMemory (CVE-2016-8862) [bsc#1007245]

notes.text: The AcquireMagickMemory function in MagickCore/memory.c in ImageMagick before 7.0.3.3 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via a crafted image, which triggers a memory allocation failure.
